---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Cody Smith | Web Management & Marketing Strategy">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative pt-40 pb-32 px-6 overflow-hidden">
    <!-- Ambient glow -->
    <div class="absolute top-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[600px] h-[400px] bg-amber-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="reveal text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-8">Cedar City, Utah</p>
      <h1 class="reveal font-serif text-5xl md:text-7xl lg:text-8xl text-neutral-100 leading-[1.05] mb-10" style="--i:1">
        Your business outgrew<br />
        <span class="gradient-text">its website</span><br class="hidden md:block" />
        a while ago.
      </h1>
      <p class="reveal text-neutral-400 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-2xl mb-14" style="--i:2">
        The site hasn't been updated in months. The analytics might be lying to you. The person who built it isn't returning your calls. I close the gap between the business you've built and the website representing it.
      </p>
      <div class="reveal flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4" style="--i:3">
        <a href="/services" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-amber-500 text-neutral-950 font-semibold text-sm rounded-lg hover:bg-amber-400 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(245,158,11,0.25)]">
          See how I work
        </a>
        <a href="/contact" class="inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 border border-white/10 text-neutral-300 font-medium text-sm rounded-lg hover:border-white/25 hover:text-neutral-100 transition-all duration-300">
          Get in touch
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I do -->
  <section class="py-32 px-6 surface-1">
    <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal mb-16">
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4">What I do</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100">Four lanes. One practice.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 reveal-stagger">
        <a href="/services/web-management" class="reveal glow-card p-8 block group cursor-pointer" style="--i:0">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs">01</span>
            <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-lg font-medium group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors duration-300">Web Management</h3>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-700 group-hover:text-amber-400 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-all duration-300 ml-auto" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" /></svg>
          </div>
          <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Your site is on shared hosting you don't control. Updates haven't been run in months. You find out it's down when a customer tells you. I take over the whole thing so none of that is your problem anymore.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/services/marketing-strategy" class="reveal glow-card p-8 block group cursor-pointer" style="--i:1">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs">02</span>
            <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-lg font-medium group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors duration-300">Marketing Strategy</h3>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-700 group-hover:text-amber-400 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-all duration-300 ml-auto" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" /></svg>
          </div>
          <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            You know your marketing could be better but you don't know where to start. There are twelve things competing for your attention and no way to tell which ones actually matter. I figure that out and tell you what to do first.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/services/implementation" class="reveal glow-card p-8 block group cursor-pointer" style="--i:2">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs">03</span>
            <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-lg font-medium group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors duration-300">Implementation</h3>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-700 group-hover:text-amber-400 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-all duration-300 ml-auto" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" /></svg>
          </div>
          <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Your forms don't connect to your CRM. Your analytics aren't tracking conversions. You need landing pages that don't exist yet. I build the things that close those gaps.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/services/training" class="reveal glow-card p-8 block group cursor-pointer" style="--i:3">
          <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
            <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs">04</span>
            <h3 class="text-neutral-100 text-lg font-medium group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors duration-300">Training</h3>
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-neutral-700 group-hover:text-amber-400 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-all duration-300 ml-auto" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" /></svg>
          </div>
          <p class="text-neutral-400 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Your team asks you to "update the website" because they don't know how. They've sat through training before and forgotten it within a week. I build programs that actually stick.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The pitch -->
  <section class="relative py-32 px-6 dot-grid">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal">
        <p class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4">The short version</p>
        <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100 mb-12">Why me.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-8 text-neutral-400 text-lg leading-relaxed">
        <p class="reveal">
          Most small businesses don't need a marketing department. They need one person who understands the whole picture. Someone who can look at the website, the analytics, the SEO, the content, and the competitive landscape, and tell them what actually matters this month.
        </p>
        <p class="reveal">
          I've spent a career absorbing adjacent problems. Writing that turned into web strategy. Web strategy that turned into marketing operations. Marketing operations that turned into training programs. Every role, the same pattern: start with the thing I was hired for, end up doing the three things nobody else was handling.
        </p>
        <p class="reveal text-neutral-100 font-quote text-2xl md:text-3xl italic">
          Now I do it on purpose.
        </p>
      </div>
      <a href="/about" class="reveal inline-flex items-center gap-3 text-amber-400 text-sm mt-12 hover:text-amber-300 transition-colors duration-300 group">
        Read the longer version
        <svg class="w-4 h-4 group-hover:translate-x-1 transition-transform duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" />
        </svg>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="relative py-32 px-6 surface-1 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[500px] h-[300px] bg-amber-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <p class="reveal text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-4">Get started</p>
      <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100 mb-6">Sound familiar?</h2>
      <p class="reveal text-neutral-400 text-lg mb-10">If you're nodding at any of this, we should talk. No pitch deck. Just a conversation about what's going on and whether I can help.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="reveal inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-amber-500 text-neutral-950 font-semibold text-sm rounded-lg hover:bg-amber-400 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(245,158,11,0.25)]">
        Start a conversation
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
